Clinton backs return of Glenn as astronaut . U . S . President Bill Clinton on Friday said he would like to see Senator John Glenn , the first American to orbit the Earth , make a return trip to space as the world ' s oldest astronaut . The 75 - year - old Glenn , who plans to retire from the Senate , has talked with Clinton about the possibility of taking another mission into space , the U . S . president told reporters onboard Air Force One enroute to Denmark from Romania . " I ' m for it . . . I think it would be a great thing , " Clinton said , noting it would provide a chance to measure the impact of weightlessness on the elderly . " I told him I ' d like to go , " Clinton said . 
